        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 6:16AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 616 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
West Greene, or 10 miles south of Aliceville, moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Aliceville, Akron, Snoddy, Ralph, Emelle, New Mount Hebron, Panola,
Walden Quarters, Eutaw Municipal Airport, George Downer Airport, West
Greene, Union, Pleasant Ridge, Lewiston, Benevola, Johnston Lake,
Eutaw, Memphis, Wedgeworth, and Gainesville Lake Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 AM CDT for
west central Alabama.</instruction>
